Responsibilities

Follow up with digital marketing service orders - Search Engine Marketing (SEM) / Social Media Marketing/ Programmatic campaigns;
Prepare proposal, budget and execution plan for marketing campaigns;
Implement and execute digital, search, display and social media campaigns;
Deliver excellent pre-sales & after-sales service to both existing and new clients;
Establish and maintain strong relationships with business partners and clients;
Adopt consultative approach to customers on their digital marketing & advertising strategies with big data research and analysis;
Responsible for the strategic development and day-to-day operation of the corporate social media and other online channels.

Requirements

Higher Diploma / Degree holders in Marketing, Business Administration, Public Relations, Information Management & Technology, E-Commerce, Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent discipline;
Experience in at least 3 years is welcomed;
Strong knowledge in Google Adwords and Google Analytics; 
Experience in digital marketing and emerging digital technology, social trends and insights;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Proactive, self-motivated and able to work independently;
Proficient in using MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint;
Good written and spoken in English and Chinese including both Cantonese and Mandarin.



AdTactics offers an attractive remuneration package, including 5 days’ work, performance bonus, bank holidays, and wedding leaves to right candidates. For interested parties please send a cover letter stating your current salary and expected salary with Resume to us.

Benefits:

5 days Work + Bank Holidays
Full Medical Coverage
Sales Incentive
Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave
Training Subsidy
Professional training in digital marketing
Fast track career progression in this growing industry

Responsibilities include:

Identify new clients and perform outbound call selling on our digital marketing consultancy service via phone;
Handle enquiries and provide service information to corporate clients in a professional manner;
Provide support to Business Development Team.

Requirements:

Passionate to digital marketing;
Diploma or above; education background in marketing/ advertising or related discipline will be an advantage;
Possessing at least 1 year of working experience is preferred;
Experience in call center/ B2B customer service is an advantage;
Proficient in both written and oral Chinese and English;
Excellent organizational and communication skills;
High level of customer centric mentality; able to work in a fast-paced environment;
Outstanding candidates will be promoted to Sales Manager after completing on-the-job-training programme.

To Apply:

For more information about You Find Ltd., please visit www.youfind.hk
We offer attractive package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your application by clicking "Apply Now".
All information received will be used for recruitment purpose only and will be kept in strict confidential.

YouFind is an Equal Opportunity Employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any kind. All employment decisions at YouFind are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race; family status; gender; disability status or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in Hong Kong.

We are a creative agency providing a wide range of advertising services. With our expertise in creative communications, social media content creation, art and design work, to stand out our client’s brand in the commercial world.

You will become an integral part of the team, cooperate with some key international and local brands and be responsible for managing various advertising campaigns.

Responsibilities
Implement marketing plans, promotion campaigns, KOLs campaigns, events, social media campaigns etc;
Responsible for day-to-day client activities and delivery of works;
Maintain excellent and long-term relationship with clients, working partners and KOLs/celebrities;
Understand client’s business & objectives and input strategically to develop creative briefs;
Coordinate with different parties to execute various advertising projects.

Requirements

Bachelor Degree in Sales & Marketing / Digital Marketing / Communications / Advertising / Public Relations or related disciplines;
1-2 years working experience in Digital Marketing or Marketing industry;
Fresh graduate are also welcome;
Willing to coordinate with various parties;
Strong communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills;
Fluent in spoken and written English, Chinese, and Putonghua;
Immediately availability is preferred.

We offer a 5-day week of work, group medical insurance coverage & birthday leave.

Interested parties, please send your detailed resume with the expected salary via Apply Now.

This role is located and based in Hong Kong. Candidates must be eligible to work in Hong Kong.

What You Will Be Doing:


Manage digital campaign projects for clients
Work closely with vendors / internal teams to plan, develop, execute and implement digital marketing campaign projects;
Manage and analyze clients' digital performance  from different industries (Beauty, Banking, Travel, FMCG, NGO, other media agencies, etc.);
Study and document client’s requirements and provide suggestions / solutions based on client’s inquiries;
Communicate and solve problem during project period with clients;
Write up reports for clients about monthly updates, campaign effectiveness, marketing outcomes, data insights, competitor analysis, etc.

 What You Need for this Position:


Degree or above in Business, Advertising, Marketing, Journalism, Media, Public Relations, Communications, Information system, E-commerce, project management or related discipline;
1-2 years solid experience in accounts servicing, preferably in managing online advertising and social media projects;
Fluent in written Chinese and English and spoken Mandarin, English and Cantonese;
Excellent communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills is a must;
Mature, attention to details and ability to work under tight timeline and multi-task independently;
Agency experiences are preferred;
Proficiency in MS office application;

 Benefits We Offer:

 5 days’ work
Quarterly Performance Bonus
Medical Coverage including Dental
Flexible Working Hours
Overtime Meal and Transportation allowance
Birthday, Wedding, Graduation and other special leaves
Fun, young and joyful environment 

