Requirements:

Bachelor degree in Advertising, Mass Communication, Marketing or related disciplines;
1 - 2 year of relevant work experience with proven capabilities of being strategic and creative in handling digital marketing campaigns;
 A natural user of social media and forums as well as natural player of mobile games
 Passionate and familiar with various online media platforms;
Good marketing sense, multi-tasking and good management;
Presentable, independent, proactive and creative;
 A good team player, able and flexible to work with people of different cultures;

Responsibilities:

- Help develop integrated digital marketing solutions for clients, including but not limited to social  media maintenance, creative campaign, video campaign, website production, O2O solution, media  placement, Social CRM, etc.

- Formulate insightful strategies and creative ideas to meet clients’ objectives, ensure successful  execution, flow and end-result.

- Prepare documents to pitch clients, e.g. marketing plan, schedule, budget etc.;

- Present ideas to clients together with the Project Management Team, if necessary;

- Explore and assimilate the latest digital marketing trends and develop knowledge management    database for internal and external training

- Assist in key client project management and coordinate communication with both internal and  external parties.

We offer performance bonus, medical coverage, bank holidays, and wedding leaves to right candidates. Interested parties please send a cover letter stating your expected salary, resume and a full set of your portfolio to Mr. Yeung. 

*All information will be treated as confidential and used solely for recruitment purposes.

Responsibility:

Handle multiple client projects such as video production, influencer activation, social media management, and other digital marketing campaigns;
Provide creative inputs in social media content and campaign planning;
Manage timeline to ensure smooth project execution;
Prepare proposals and support new clients pitching;
Liaise with and provide creative briefings to vendors, designers, internal and external parties;
Monitor project implementation and performance against KPIs;
Compile regular and post-campaign reports for project performance evaluations;
Stay alert to industry happenings and able to share insights; 

Requirement: 

Degree in Media, Marketing, Communications or related discipline;
Minimum 1 year experience on digital/social media management or other relevant work experience;
Demonstrate strong communication and presentation skills;
Familiar with the social media & influencer landscape and practices in Hong Kong; 
Proficiency in written and spoken English and Chinese; 
Proactive, passionate, and a detail-minded team player;
Good multi-tasking skills, willing to work under pressure and tight schedules;
Experience working with social listening and social media management tools is a plus;  
Immediate availability is highly preferred;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Account Executive;

All personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.

WHAT YOU WILL BE WORKING ON:
Build strong, long-term client relationships and maintain frequent contact;
Perform fundamental support for pitch, proposal and projects on a local and international basis;
Formulate and execute marketing strategy to drive e-Commerce business on online platforms;
Coordinate with internal team to execute digital marketing campaigns including creative copywriting, media evaluation, campaign trafficking, media buy, optimizing and reporting;
Plan and execute digital marketing campaigns including SEO/SEM, social media and display advertising to increase sales and brand awareness;
Plan and manage advertising cost and marketing budget to obtain ROI optimization;
Maintain social media presence for brands across multiple digital channels like Facebook, Instagram…etc;
Monitor performance daily and execute optimisation strategies;
Explore and identify new channel expansion opportunities to reach potential customers;
Perform analysis on the marketing results to optimize customer experience across multiple channels: offline to online and vice versa;
YOUR SKILLSET AND BACKGROUND:
Hands-on experience in Google Ads, Facebook Manager or any other relevant tools
Comfortable with numbers.
You are hands-on, details oriented and organized
You are a team player and able to communicate effectively and build solid relationships with clients and colleagues
You are curious at heart and like to take ownership of something to make it better day to day basis with a demonstrated ability to build positive relationships with peers
“Can do” attitude and disciplined and proactive approach to work



Interested parties please email detail resume with recent portfolio, current and expected salary to recruit(@)digitpepper.com
Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only

Planning



Assist the Manager to develop media strategy, channel/ platform recommendations and prepare the detailed media flow-plan;
Leverage available planning tools and liaise with media owners for proposals;
Engage clients on day to day operations, media trend updates and various campaign reports on local/regional/global levels.

Buying



Negotiate with media owners for better rates and value adds;
Book ads - both managed service and self-service across various platforms;
Liaise with media vendors & creative agencies for material submission;
Digital ad ops (campaign set up on self-serve platforms, tagging of ads and client's site, ensure ads are properly served and tags are firing);
Global ops (adhering and following globally set parameters and campaign execution processes while also guiding others);
Oversee all performance across channels (Search, Social, Programmatic etc.);
Monitor and optimize performance during campaign period across platforms such as Google Adwords, Facebook, LinkedIn etc.
Weekly digital reporting, end of campaign reporting and reconciliation of final costs for finance billings.

Qualifications


1 - 3 years' of digital media experience
Meticulous, good with numbers and able to organise and prioritise tasks and work under tight timelines
Resilient to change and willing to keen to learn new skills
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal, with internal and external parties
Ready to take up initiatives and ownership of projects
Play well with others and are a team player
Good command of English and Chinese

