About Us


Hi, we are [‘mediPr], a young, dynamic and fast-growing medical communications agency. We help pharmaceutical companies, clinics, and other medical organisations with event management, content creation, and video production. 

We are growing, and looking for a self-motivated account manager to join our team. In return, we offer an excellent commission system. 

Job Overview

Interested to join our young and growing team? We are looking for a bright personality who is customer focused and with a strong sense of responsibility. You enjoy the challenge of finding business opportunities with existing and new clients, you are keen to meet business targets, and you thrive when you can communicate and work with your colleagues to deliver a product within budget, scope, and timelines. 

Responsibilities and Duties

B2B sales;
Generate sales strategies and achieve sales targets;
Develop and explore business and marketing opportunities within the pharmaceutical and medical devices industry as well as clinics and healthcare organisations;
Maintain a good relationship with existing and new clients within the pharmaceutical and medical devices industries as well as with healthcare providers;
Project management, liaise with internal team members to ensure project deliverables are of high quality and met within budget and timelines.

Qualifications

You hold a bachelor’s degree, or higher. Candidates with prior sales or accounts experience within the pharmaceutical industry or for a medical communications agency are preferred.

Personal Characteristics and Skills Required

You are proactive and punctual with customer-focused attitude, problem-solving mentality, and a strong sense of responsibility and business acumen;
You are self-motivated with the ability to work independently and in a team environment;
You are outgoing and persuasive with good communication and presentation skills;
You are a permanent resident of Hong Kong, native in Cantonese, proficient in English. Spoken Mandarin is a positive.

What we Offer

An excellent and competitive package consisting of basic salary plus tiered commission;
An opportunity to grow and help grow. We are growing the company, the successful candidate is offered an option to grow with us;
A five-day workweek with an excellent work-life balance. 

Reporting Line

The successful incumbent will report to the Director of [‘mediPr].

Process

Please submit your resume, cover letter, and current and desired salary. Candidates who do not hear back from Company within two (2) weeks after submission of the documents may consider their application to be unsuccessful.
